tracks.name: Ruta 33 from Callejón de Ordaiz via Los Pedacitos and Santa Catalina
tracks.description: A scenic coastal and valley route through Hermigua's lush agricultural landscapes. Starting from the dramatic Callejón de Ordaiz gorge, the trail winds through terraced banana plantations and traditional hamlets. The moderate ascent (254m elevation gain) around the 3km mark leads through Los Pedacitos before reaching the historic village of Santa Catalina.
tracks.highlights: Hermigua Valley views, banana terraces, Callejón de Ordaiz ravine, traditional Canarian architecture
tracks.difficulty: Moderate - one sustained 11% climb at 3km with 173m ascent

tracks.name: GR 132 from Palmarejo to Vallehermoso via Agulo
tracks.description: The famous coastal GR 132 trail offering spectacular Atlantic views and dramatic elevation changes (778m total gain). Starting from Palmarejo, the trail hugs dramatic cliffs before a challenging ascent to Agulo, one of La Gomera's most picturesque villages perched on the mountainside. Multiple steep sections with grades up to 18.5% lead through laurel forest before descending to Vallehermoso.
tracks.highlights: Agulo village, coastal cliffs, Atlantic panoramas, UNESCO laurel forest, Roque de Agando views
tracks.difficulty: Strenuous - three major climbs between 3-6km with grades up to 18.5%, total 778m elevation gain

tracks.name: GR 132 from Vallehermoso via La Quilla, Epina, and Arguamul
tracks.description: A challenging circular route through Vallehermoso's mountainous backcountry (631m elevation gain). The trail climbs steeply to La Quilla, then traverses high terraced landscapes through the ancient hamlets of Epina and Arguamul. Early steep sections (16-17% grades) are rewarded with expansive views of the northern coast and Garajonay massif.
tracks.highlights: Vallehermoso Canyon, terraced agricultural zones, traditional mountain villages, Garajonay views
tracks.difficulty: Strenuous - two major climbs in first 3km with grades up to 16.8%

tracks.name: GR131 from Vallehermoso to Temocodá via Rosa de las Piedras
tracks.description: The most challenging ascent of your trip on the legendary GR131 trans-island trail (891m elevation gain). Starting from sea-level Vallehermoso, the route climbs relentlessly through multiple ecosystems. The iconic Rosa de las Piedras rock formation marks the entrance to the high mountain zone before reaching Temocodá at over 1,000m elevation. Three sustained steep sections with grades up to 19.3%.
tracks.highlights: Rosa de las Piedras rock formations, dramatic altitude zones, cloud forest transition, panoramic summit views
tracks.difficulty: Very Strenuous - three major climbs including a brutal 19.3% section at 4.5km, 891m total elevation gain

tracks.name: Ruta 15 from Temocodá via El Cercado, Las Viñas, and La Vizcaína
tracks.description: A high-altitude traverse through La Gomera's central highlands (744-1,144m), passing through traditional pottery villages. The route explores El Cercado, famous for its ceramic artisans, continues through vine-covered Las Viñas, and winds through La Vizcaína's pine forests. Gentler gradients but significant elevation due to the high-altitude undulating terrain.
tracks.highlights: El Cercado pottery workshops, highland agriculture, pine forests, central plateau vistas
tracks.difficulty: Moderate-Challenging - sustained high altitude with one steep 11.7% climb near the end

tracks.name: GR131 from Temocodá via Erque and Igualero
tracks.description: The highest elevation hike of your journey, reaching 1,470m on the GR131 ridge. This spectacular mountain traverse follows ancient paths through Erque and Igualero, remote hamlets clinging to steep mountainsides. The route offers panoramic views across the entire island and to neighboring Tenerife and El Teide volcano. Despite the altitude, gradients are more moderate due to traversing along the ridgeline.
tracks.highlights: Highest point of the trip (1,470m), El Teide views, remote mountain villages, island-wide panoramas, ridge walking
tracks.difficulty: Challenging - high altitude (944-1,470m) with thinner air, but gentler gradients than earlier GR131 sections
